Mediatools is a collection of audio and video processing blocks for use in GNU Radio.

Dependencies include:

    libavcodec-dev
    libavformat-dev
    libavutil-dev

    on ubuntu:
        sudo apt-get install libavcodec-dev libavformat-dev libavutil-dev

    these are all part of the ffmpeg project

Any audio input codec supported by ffmpeg should work, so this source should be cabable of playing mixed playlists of mp3, ogg, flac, wav, wmv, or any other input audio codecs you can build support for in ffmpeg


